{"detail":{"ID":1019,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-03 20:09:10","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-03 20:09:10","post_content":"The <em>Town Square<\/em>\u00a0was conceived to embody the ideal that \u201cevery step you take is the goal you seek\u201d and meant as a celebration of children in movement. The spiral ramp is lined with a curved glass railing facing inward and portholes facing outward. These portholes offer glimpses into the rest of the museum, sparking imagination and building excitement for what is to come. It directs visitors from the main entrance of the museum intuitively down into its center on the main exhibit floor, all the while stretching distance and multiplying views into the activity below. Suspended from the roof of the building, this giant wooden chandelier touches the floor below at one gentle point. Skylights filter light in from the park above.","post_title":"<p>Town Square Children's Museum, Chicago, US 2010<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"town-square-chicago-childrens-museum-il-2010","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-06-07 19:51:24","post_modified_gmt":"2017-06-07 19:51:24","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=1019","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","ancestors":[],"page_template":"","post_category":[],"tags_input":[],"extended":{"year":"","images":[{"image":{"width":1500,"height":927,"file":"2017\/04\/OBRA_TOWN_SQUARE_02.jpg","sizes":{"thumbnail":{"file":"OBRA_TOWN_SQUARE_02-760x460.jpg","width":760,"height":460,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"medium":{"file":"OBRA_TOWN_SQUARE_02-300x185.jpg","width":300,"height":185,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"medium_large":{"file":"OBRA_TOWN_SQUARE_02-768x475.jpg","width":768,"height":475,"mime-type":"image\/jpeg"},"large":{"file":"OBRA_TOWN_SQUARE_02-1500x927.jpg","wi